Pakistan rupee plunges in kerb after devaluation . The Pakistani rupee opened 1 . 95 rupees down at 42 . 50 to the dollar on Tuesday in the kerb market after the central bank devalued the rupee 7 . 86 percent against the dollar , dealers said . The State ( central ) Bank of Pakistan ( SBP ) moved the rupee to 40 . 1200 / 40 . 3206 to the dollar from 36 . 9700 / 37 . 1549 . It last changed the rate on September 10 . " The market is very volatile at the moment , " dealer Owais Kalia said , adding that the rupee could slide further , but profit - taking in dollars was also expected . - - Ovais Subhani 9221 - 5685192 
